  <h3>Short biography <em><a href="/the-researcher" target="_blank">by Louise Watson</a></em></h3>
<p><span class="emphasis">Raphaelle Obomsawin</span> is a young abenakis from Odanak.
  Growing up in a non-traditional environment, her curiosity for her indigenous origins started by participating
  in archeological excavations in her community. She then joined the Kiuna college, studying among other First Nations
  and receving a specialised education. When I first met herShe graduated in 2016 from the Social Sciences Program and pursued a bachelor
  in applied education. Raphaelle practices arts in various disciplines: crafting, beading, singing and writing.
  The interview has been conducted in Odanak, in August 2016 (recorded, edited and translated by Louise Watson)

 </p>
