<div class="col-xs-6">
<p> «When I was going go secondary school, I didn’t tell to anyone that I was indigenous, if I was asked questions, I didn’t know anything. I knew my community was called Odanak, and that was it.»
</br></br>(...)</br></br>«Now, I can really interact with people in my community, whereas I had never thought I would interact with them before, because being indigenous wasn’t part of my identity.Today, it’s really something I want to develop about myself, and I’m not done learning about it. »</p>
